        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-26 21:31:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nProblem is caused by a leak of the in-flight request counter caused by http://review.whamcloud.com/10223 and http://review.whamcloud.com/10706.\n\nPatch http://review.whamcloud.com/10828 has the fix, but it is still good to be more robust in error handling.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "b09862369b98d1e86e8bd5d4fbf3e0943e79a2ea",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-26 22:03:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2\n\nThe conf-sanity.sh failure is LU-5244 but without the LASSERT:\n\n osp_sync_thread()) t32fs-OST0000-osc-MDT0000: syn_rpc_in_progress=5 syn_prc_in_flight=5 syn_commited_there:empty\n\nhttps://old-testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/943eb528-fce5-11e3-827a-52540035b04c",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "7500e7065618b3ee343b302a6b7e414378b57775",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-27 12:51:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nI'm not sure that livelock is any better than LASSERT. say, due to a mistake in RPC accounting we got stuck here and can't umount the filesystem. and the user has to reboot anyway?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "7edc5bc90bce0f5ed565990bccea7123bfeebe65",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-27 17:38:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nPer Alex's last comment I wonder if it makes sense to keep the LASSERT()?  This indeed turned out to be caused by a reference leak that would never have been fixed by waiting longer (contrary to my initial thoughts), and LASSERT() would at least allow the MDS to reboot and failover.\n\nMarking -1 until we resolve the discussion.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "1d25db64d8d4ad223b562447716a2d1a31bde6a0",
